{
  "doc_id": "24986",
  "text": "As mentioned above, CCK2 receptor is distributed both in the CNS and in peripheral tissues and plays an essential role in vital physiological functions [1, [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] 43] . In in vitro studies, CCK2R is often expressed ectopically in cell lines such as CHO-K1, as has been done previously by others [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . In the present work, CCK stimulation of CCK2R-CHO-K1 cells was found to trigger regular calcium oscillations, which were inhibited completely by the CCK2R antagonist YM 022 (Figure 1 ). CCK-induced CCK2R desensitization, especially after prolonged stimulation at higher CCK concentrations, could particularly be noted (Figures 1 and 4 ). All of these data confirm that the CCK2R we expressed heterologously in CHO-K1 cells was the quintessential CCK2 receptor.",
